<HEADLINE> URGENT  Kenya President to Name Vice-president </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NAIROBI, April 1 (Xinhua) -- Kenyan President Daniel arap Moi
Thursday said he will soon appoint a vice-president, breaking the
14-month silence on the vacant seat of vice-president.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at the Jomo Kenyatta International Airport on arrival
from a tour of Namibia and Malawi, Moi said the decision to fill
the number two post, which has remained vacant since last January,
has been goaded by the anxiety of kenyans over the absence of a
vice president.
</P>
<P>
The head of state also dismissed as unnecessary fears that
Kenya is at risk should he die in office before appointing a
deputy. 
</P>
</TEXT>
