<DOCNO> XIE19990402.0005 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-04-02 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Eleven European FMs Call for Urgent Aid for Kosovo </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BONN April 1 (Xinhua)--The European Troika Foreign Ministers
with their counterparts from 8 Southeast European countries
Thursday after a meeting appealed closest cooperation between the
states and organizations involved to supply urgent aid for Kosovo
refugees.
</P>
<P>
The meeting, in German town of Petersberg, on humanitarian
issues and stability in Balkan region was held between European
Troika and Albania, Bosnia, Bulgaria, Croatia, Macedonia of
Federal Yugoslavia, Hungary, Romania, Slovenia.
</P>
<P>
Top goal of the meeting was to coordinate measures to stabilize
the region and improve the situation of Kosovo refugees.
</P>
<P>
The European Union (EU) commissar for humanitarian issues Emma
Bonino, the United Nations (UN) refugee commissar Sadako Ogata,
and officials of the Organization for Security and Cooperation in
Europe (OSCE) took part in the meeting.
</P>
<P>
Foreign Ministers said the refugees' needs for food, medical
equipment, equipment for camps and means for transportation should
be met immediately. They called on the NATO to contribute to
humanitarian aid by making available helicopters to transport
refugees and supplies.
</P>
<P>
In the EU presidency statement distributed after the meeting,
the European Troika said that EU would continue its efforts to
help stabilizing the region "in all possible ways".
</P>
<P>
The European Troika stands for Austria, Germany and Finland,
which are respectively the former, present and next rotating
president of EU.
</P>
<P>
A regular airlift will be established to bring supplies to the
refugees, and the European Commission Kosovo Crisis Team will be
reinforced to deal with the refugee issues, the statement said.
</P>
<P>
German Foreign Minister Joschka Fischer told the press
conference after the meeting, that the EU will "directly and
quickly" help the countries neighboring Yugoslavia to deal with
tens of thousands of refugees that flood in.
</P>
<P>
Fischer stressed that the emergent measure of the EU is to
provide Albania and Macedonia with payments aid, while refugees
have made extraordinary burdens to the two countries and direct
aid of food and medical equipment is hard to organize. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
