<HEADLINE> Chinese Projects Suitable for Mozambique: </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MAPUTO, April 1 (Xinhua) -- Mozambican Prime Minister Pascoal
Mocumbi said here Thursday that the Chinese-sponsored projects in
agriculture and pharmaceutics are suitable for the need of
Mozambique.
</P>
<P>
Mocumbi said this while meeting with Zhang Delin, Party
Secretary of the Chongqing Municipality of China, who is leading a
delegation of the Chinese city on a field trip in the southern
African country.
</P>
<P>
Despite fast development, Mozambique is still a poor country
and most of its people are still facing the problems of food,
clothes and medicine shortage, the prime minister noted.
</P>
<P>
The cooperation projects initiated by Chongqing in agriculture
and pharmaceutics will help Mozambique in alleviating food
shortage and fighting against various diseases, he said.
</P>
<P>
Other projects such as ship building and repairing, and radio
making are also necessary for the Mozambican markets, he added.
</P>
<P>
He expressed his hope that the entrepreneurs from both nations
will invest jointly in the business orientated for the markets in
Mozambique and the southern Africa region.
</P>
<P>
The prime minister also said that he hopes Chongqing and one of
 Mozambican cities can become sister cities.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese delegation, which arrived in Maputo on March 25,
spent one week in capital Maputo, central province of Sofala and
northern province of Nampula to assess the conditions for
investment and cooperation.
</P>
<P>
In Sofala, Chongqing and the Mozambican side signed a
memorandum on comprehensive development in agriculture and
forestry.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese city is willing to bring new technologies in
growing rice, corn and vegetables to Mozambique to help promote
local economic development and improve the living standards of the
Mozambican people, Zhang said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
