<HEADLINE> Private Air Transport Company Begins Operation in </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, April 1 (Xinhua) -- Abyssinia Air Service, a
private air transport company, was officially inaugurated here
Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Abyssinia Air Service began its operation with a 13-seater
passenger plane which was imported three weeks ago.
</P>
<P>
Company owner Captain Solomon Gizaw said the private company
was set up at a cost of 13.5 million birr (about 1.7 million U.S.
dollars).
</P>
<P>
He said the company has plans to import another aircraft
shortly.
</P>
<P>
Taddesse Haile, General Manager of Ethiopian Investment
Authority said at the inaugural ceremony that the expansion of air
transport service is crucial for the growth of the country's
economy in general and the tourism industry in particular.
</P>
<P>
First private air company was established in Ethiopia at the
end of 1997 and there are five private air companies in the
country.  
</P>
