<HEADLINE> Canada Provides Grant for Burundi Peace Process </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DAR ES SALAAM, April 1 (Xinhua) -- The Canadian government has
provided a grant of one million Canadian dollars (about 663,000
U.S. dollars) to the Mwalimu Nyerere Foundation, an agency
dedicated to the Burundi peace process.
</P>
<P>
The fund has been channelled through the Canadian International
 Development Agency (CIDA), according to a statement issued here
Thursday by the foundation, which is led by Tanzania's former
president Julius Nyerere.
</P>
<P>
Earlier this month, Canada had contributed 750,000 Canadian
dollars to the Dar es Salaam-based foundation, said the statement.
</P>
<P>
The foundation has extended thanks to the government of Canada
and the CIDA as a funding agency for the continued moral and
financial support to the Burundi peace process under the
facilitation of Nyerere.
</P>
<P>
Since last year, four rounds of Burundi peace talks have been
held under the chairmanship of Nyerere to bring an end to the war
which has reportedly killed more than 150,000 people in the tiny
central African country. 
</P>
</TEXT>
