<HEADLINE> Ethiopia Secures $1.1Billion for 5-Year Road </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, April 1 (Xinhua) -- The Ethiopian Road Authority
said Thursday that a 1.1 billion-U.S. dollar grant has been
secured from the World Bank, the European Union and other donor
countries for the five-year road development program of the Horn
of Africa country.
</P>
<P>
General Manager of the road authority, Tesfamichael Nahusenary,
said that the five-year road program plans to increase the total
mileage of asphalt, highway and feeder roads to 30,300 kilometers
in 2001/02 from 24, 000 km in 1997/98.
</P>
<P>
Tesfamichael told reporters that the authority is undertaking
the construction and maintenance of 572 km highways and feeder
roads at a cost of over 139 million U.S. dollars.
</P>
<P>
He said that the authority is implementing on its own the
construction of 122 km asphalt roads, maintenance of 140 km
highways and the construction and renovation of 145 km feeder
roads.
</P>
<P>
He added that the remaining 165 km asphalt and feeder roads are
being constructed by foreign contractors. 
</P>
</TEXT>
