<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Strange Child Disease Kills 3 in Angola </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUANDA, April 1 (Xinhua) -- A strange disease which often
endangers children under six of age, rendering many of those
sufferers paralyzed, is found in Angola, the health department
announced Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The National Bureau of Public Health said in a statement that
three children have died of the disease and as many as 57 from
neighboring cities of the capital, have lost their ability to
stand up or walk since mid-March.
</P>
<P>
Symptoms of the disease look like that of cold, the statement
said, but it warn that children affected with the strange disease
should never be treated as cold suffers, as the normal injection
of cold medicine might speed up the process of paralyzation.
</P>
<P>
Calls for aid have been sent to the international society, the
statement said, adding that the number of children affected with
the disease is growing.
</P>
<P>
It is reported that South African doctors have found a kind of
parasitic virus from excrement sample sent to South Africa.
</P>
</TEXT>
