<HEADLINE> Ugandan Bank Suspends Operation in Tanzania </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DAR ES SALAAM, April 1 (Xinhua) -- The operation of the
Uganda's Greenland Bank branch in Tanzania was suspended Thursday
and its administration has been taken over by Tanzania's central
bank.
</P>
<P>
The Bank of Tanzania (BoT), said in a statement that the action
was taken after the Bank of Uganda informed it that Greenland Bank
(Uganda) Limited will now be closed down on April 1.
</P>
<P>
Considering the potential effect that the closure may have on
the operations of Greenland Bank (T) Limited, the BoT has taken
over the administration of Greenland Bank effective on the same
day, the statement said.
</P>
<P>
"While under the administration of the Bank of Tanzania, all
operations of Greenland Bank (T) Limited shall cease until further
notice," it said.
</P>
<P>
On December 6 last year, the Bank of Uganda took over the
administration of Greenland Bank (Uganda) Limited. Following that
action the BoT said it has been closely watching over the
operations of Greenland Bank (Tanzania) Limited which has been
operating normally.
</P>
<P>
One client, Conrad Dunstan, said he is surprised to see the
bank suspended when he went to draw his money. He said Greenland's
suspension will affect many people who are prepared to spend the
Easter festival. 
</P>
</TEXT>
