<HEADLINE> Li Peng Arrives in Crete to Continue Official Visit </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CRETE (GREECE), April 1 (Xinhua) -- Li Peng, chairman of the
Standing Committee of the National People's Congress of China,
arrived in the southern Greek island of Crete Thursday afternoon
from Athens to continue his four-day official visit to Greece.
</P>
<P>
Li Peng was warmly greeted at the airport by Crete Governor
Vasilis Valsopoulos and other senior officials.
</P>
<P>
During his meeting with Valsopoulos shortly after his arrival,
Li Peng said that as countries of civilization with long history,
China and Greece made remarkable contributions to the civilization
and progress of mankind.
</P>
<P>
He said that his current visit here is to further strengthen
mutual understanding and friendship, and to push forward the
development of the relations between the two countries.
</P>
<P>
He also said that during his talks with Greek President Costis
Stephanopoulos, Prime Minister Costas Simitis and President of the
Parliament Apostolos Kaklamanis in Athens over the past days, they
reached a wide-ranging agreement on bilateral ties and issues of
common concern, such as the crisis in Yugoslavia.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese leader expressed the hope that China and Greece
make joint efforts to push forward the friendly and cooperative
relationship between the two countries.
</P>
<P>
Describing Li Peng's current visit as "a successful one,"
Valsopoulos said that the people of the Crete island have good
feelings toward the Chinese people. He hopes that more Chinese
people will come and visit the island.
</P>
<P>
Li Pend arrived in Greece Tuesday afternoon for an official
visit, which will also bring him to Turkey, Syria, Pakistan,
Bangladesh and Thailand. 
</P>
