<DOCNO> XIE19990402.0025 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-04-02 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> New Food Aid Convention to Come Into Effect in July </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, April 1 (Xinhua) -- Members of the Food Aid Committee
have completed the negotiation of a new Food Aid Convention (FAC),
the International Grains Council (IGC) announced Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The members of the 1999 Food Aid Convention are Argentina,
Australia, Canada, the European Community and its member states,
Japan, Norway, Switzerland and America.
</P>
<P>
The IGC said in a statement: subject to the necessary actions
by member governments, the new FAC will come into effect on 1 July
1999.
</P>
<P>
The main objective of the 1999 Food Aid Convention is "to
contribute to world food security and to improve the ability of
the international community to respond to emergency food
situations and other food needs of developing countries,"
according to the statement.
</P>
<P>
FAC members will make quality food aid available to developing
countries with the greatest needs on a predictable basis,
irrespective of fluctuations in world food prices and supplies.
</P>
<P>
Particular importance is attached to ensuring that food aid is
directed to the alleviation of poverty and hunger of the most
vulnerable groups, the IGC said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
