<HEADLINE> ADB Loan Important for Promotion of Pak Trade, Export </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, April 1 (Xinhua) -- The approval of a 300 million
U.S. dollar loan by the Asian Development Bank (ADB) to Pakistan
is an important stride towards liberalizing import and freer trade
in the country, ADB sources here said Thursday.
</P>
<P>
ADB announced Wednesday that it had cleared a 300 million
dollar loan to Pakistan to support the country's trade, export
promotion and industry program.
</P>
<P>
The first tranche of 200 million dollars of the ADB loan
approved Wednesday was disbursed on the same day.
</P>
<P>
Sources at the ADB resident mission here said the loan for
trade, export promotion and industry will lessen chronic trade and
industry distortions in Pakistan.
</P>
<P>
The trade, export promotion and industry program will
rationalize tariffs, remove non-tariff barriers and give exporters
better excess to imported inputs and finance at market prices, the
sources added.
</P>
<P>
The ADB loan will also modernize export policies and improve
the administration, said the sources.
</P>
<P>
This would slash Pakistan's dependence on import substitution
and lay the foundation for export promotion by placing domestic
players on an equal footing with foreign competitors, they noted.
</P>
<P>
The program will also support the implementation of the new
investment policy and the privatization of public manufacturing
enterprises.
</P>
<P>
It is part of the medium-term economic reform program supported
by the International Monetary Fund, the World Bank and the ADB.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
