<HEADLINE> Wanda, Shenhua Still Winless </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 1 (Xinhua) -- Defending champion Dalian Wanda
and last season's runners-up Shanghai Shenhua kept unbeaten in the
new season as both were held draws on Thursday in the third round
of the Chinese soccer league.
</P>
<P>
Wanda, four-time champion of the five-year league, drew with
Shenzhen Ping'an 1-1 in Shenzhen, Guangdong Province, collecting
just two points from two draws and one loss and wandering at the
10th place in the 14-team standings.
</P>
<P>
Shenhua got its third ties of the season when the team was held
a goalless draw by Shandong Luneng in Jinan, Shandong Province to
stay in the middle of the standings.
</P>
<P>
Beijing Guo'an and Sichuan Quanxing is sharing the top place of
the league with seven points as Guo'an defeated Wuhan Heart K 1-0
in Wuhan, Hubei Province, and Quanxing beat Qingdao Hainiu 2-0 at
home in Chengdu.
</P>
<P>
Liaoning Fushun, who returned to the top level of the Chinese
soccer after two-year spell in the second division, stepped down
to the third place on goals difference with the leading duo after
a 1-1 draw with Shenyang Haishi in Shenyang.
</P>
<P>
The fourth place went to Guangzhou Songri, who beat Chongqing
Longxin 1-0 at home in Guiyang, Guizhou Province, followed by
Jilin Aodong, who tied with Tianjin Taida 1-1 in Changchun, Jilin
Province. 
</P>
</TEXT>
