accused Turkey of harming Yugoslavia's territorial integrity and
sovereignty by joining in NATO military actions.
</P>
<P>
In an interview with the Daily News published Thursday,
Tanascovic said that by taking part in NATO military operations
against Yugoslavia, Turkey was practically working against
Yugoslavia's territorial integrity and sovereignty.
(BC-Turkey-Yugoslavia)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
ANKARA -- The Turkish government has given the green light to a
Russian naval squadron to pass through its straits into the
Mediterranean Sea in early April.
</P>
<P>
A statement issued by the Foreign Ministry Wednesday night said
the Russian embassy in Ankara had presented two requests for the
passage of eight Russian warships through its straits.
</P>
<P>
The fleet will include a missile carrier, anti-submarine
frigates and other escort vessels from the Black Sea Fleet.
(BC-Turkey-Russia-Warships)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
