Thursday the passage of Russian warships through Turkish straits
to the Mediterranean Sea or the Adriatic Sea would recover the
morale of Serbia.
</P>
<P>
Ecevit told reporters that the deployment of the Russian
warships to the region might also embolden Belgrade to kill
ethnic Albanians in the warring Serbian province of Kosovo.
(BC-Turkey-Russia)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
JERUSALEM -- The Palestinian National Authority (PNA) Thursday
sharply criticized a Israeli decision on closing Palestinian
institutions in East Jerusalem, saying it was nothing but
aggressive measures against the Palestinians.
</P>
<P>
In a statement issued in Gaza, the PNA said "the Israeli
decision was a challenge to international legitimacy," stressing
that "Jerusalem forms a red line that can not be overridden," the
Voice of Palestine reported. (BC-Israel-PNA)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
CAIRO -- Palestinian leader Yasser Arafat said Thursday the
Palestinians are still consulting with friendly countries on the
possible declaration of a Palestinian state on May 4.
</P>
<P>
"The issue of declaring the Palestinian state is still a point
of discussion with Palestinians' friends and brothers," Arafat
said after a meeting with Egyptian President Hosni Mubarak in the
Sinai resort of Sharm el-Sheikh. (BC-Egypt-Palestinians-Statehood)
</P>
