<HEADLINE> Clinton Vows to Gain Return of Three Captured U.S. </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, April 1 (Xinhua) -- President Bill Clinton pledged
Thursday that the United States will do everything in its power to
gain the return of three Army soldiers captured near the
Yugoslav-Macedonia border.
</P>
<P>
Yugoslav President Slobodan "Milosevic should make no mistake:
We will hold him and his government responsible for their safety
and their well-being," Clinton said to emotional applause from
service members gathered in a hangar at Norfolk Naval Base in
Virginia State of the country.
</P>
<P>
Shortly before Clinton spoke, Yugoslav state-controlled
television announced that the three soldiers would face criminal
proceedings before a military court on Friday.
</P>
<P>
The television showed the American soldiers, saying that they
were captured within the border of Yugoslavia when on a
reconnaissance mission on Wednesday night.
</P>
<P>
"There was absolutely no basis for them to be taken," Clinton
said. "There is no basis for them to be held. There is certainly
no basis for them to be tried." 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
