<HEADLINE> First TV Station Inaugurated in Malawi </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NAIROBI, April 1 (Xinhua) -- Malawian President Bakili Muluzi
inaugurated the first national television station in the country
in Blantyre Thursday, a report reaching here said.
</P>
<P>
Muluzi described the launching of the television station as a
landmark for his government's efforts to promote freedom of
expression.
</P>
<P>
"We made sure that this project comes to pass in order to
promote freedom of expression in the couVtry" of over 10 million
people, he was quoted as saying.
</P>
<P>
Visiting Kenyan President Daniel arap Moi witnessed the
inauguration. He advised the Malawians to use television as a
tool for development, not as a platform to promote violence and
immorality.
</P>
<P>
Muluzi noted that he would make sure professional ethics are
followed at the state-run station, saying that "this will never be
allowed to be a chewgum of immorality and violence."
</P>
<P>
According to a survey, there are some 40,000 TV sets in the
southern African country, which means that the newly-launched
television station will have some 250,000 viewers. 
</P>
</TEXT>
