<DOCNO> XIE19990402.0049 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-04-02 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Kenya President to Name Vice-president Soon </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NAIROBI, April 1 (Xinhua) -- Kenyan President Daniel arap Moi
Thursday said that he will soon appoint a vice-president, breaking
his 14-month silence on the vacant seat of vice-presidency.
</P>
<P>
"I will soon name a vice president so that we can see if your
grumbling and fears will end," Moi said. "But even if I appoint a
vice-president, the number of pans of maize meal you cook in your
homes will not increase."
</P>
<P>
Speaking at the Jomo Kenyatta International Airport on arrival
from a tour of Namibia and Malawi, Moi said his decision to fill
the number two post, which has remained vacant since last January,
has been goaded by the anxiety of Kenyans over the absence of a
vice president.
</P>
<P>
The head of state also dismissed as unnecessary worries that
Kenya is at risk should he die in office before appointing a
deputy.
</P>
<P>
The absence of a vice president has become the hottest issue in
recent days.
</P>
<P>
Kenyan leading newspapers have been carrying front-page news
stories entitled as "Give Us A VP!", "17 MPs Say No to An Extra
Moi Term" and the like.
</P>
<P>
The Kenyan opposition parties have indicted Moi for failing to
appoint a vice-president as stipulated by the current
constitution.
</P>
<P>
A legislator from the opposition party, Ford-Kenya, has
submitted a motion of a censure of Moi to Kenyan National Assembly
(Parliament) ahead of its April 6 reopening after the adjournment
since last Christmas.
</P>
<P>
The opposition parties alleged that Moi's non-compliance with
the constitution affected negatively on the constitutional review
process.
</P>
<P>
They also argued that there was no constitutional basis for Moi
to stay in office beyond the year 2002.
</P>
<P>
They opposed any attempt to change the current constitution to
allow Moi to serve an extra term.
</P>
<P>
Kenyan political observers believed that Moi's promise to name
a vice- president is meant to appease the debate.
</P>
<P>
In his previous 1992-1997 term, he appointed a weak figure from
Masai tribe as his deputy. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
