<HEADLINE> Gunmen Fail Assassination Attempt on Kaunda </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, April 1 (Xinhua) -- Gunmen Thursday night failed
in an assassination attempt on former Zambian president Kenneth
Kaunda outside his home in Lusaka, South African Press Association
(SAPA) reported.
</P>
<P>
Three gunmen approached Kaunda's car, which was being driven by
three of his security guards, as it pulled up outside his official
residence at about 8.15 p.m. (18:15 GMT), SAPA quoted Kaunda's
son, Wezi Kaunda, as saying.
</P>
<P>
Three gunmen opened fire at the vehicle. The guards lay on the
floor of the car and were unhurt.
</P>
<P>
The car was riddled with bullets and the passenger window
shattered, said Kaunda's son. The gunmen then sped off.
</P>
<P>
Kaunda was at home at the time of the incident. His son said
he had been fasting due to the recent death of his sister.
</P>
</TEXT>
