<HEADLINE> Europe's Main Markets Enjoy Strong Performances </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON April 1 (Xinhua) - Encouraged by Wall Street's solid
early start, all three Europe's main stock markets enjoyed strong
performances Thursday.
</P>
<P>
London's FTSE 100 closed 35 points higher at 6330, just over 5
points short of its record finish March 11. Earlier in the session
the blue chips had hit a new intra-day high of 6370.1, beating the
previous best of 6365.4 set March 12.
</P>
<P>
The London market had also been generously supported the
session by strength in the key pharmaceutical, financial and
telecom sectors.
</P>
<P>
Glaxo Wellcome shares closed up 82p at 2158p, a rise of 4
percent, while Zeneca added 109p, or 3.7 percent, at 3037p.
</P>
<P>
Banking group Barclays (BARC) closed 4.6 percent higher at
1856, while mobile phone stock Orange (ORA) put on 3.75 percent to
899 pence.
</P>
<P>
Germany's benchmark Xetra DAX index ended substantially
stronger after spending most of the day trapped in weaker ground.
The index ended up 36.54 points, or 0.75 percent at 4901.81
points.
</P>
<P>
French shares also opened lower, only to recover by the end of
trading. The Cac 40 index of leading shares ended up 31.97 points
at 4229.85. 
</P>
</TEXT>
