<HEADLINE> Chinese Vice President Meets ROK Parliamentarians </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 2 (Xinhua) -- Chinese Vice President Hu Jintao
met with a parliamentary delegation from the Republic of Korea (
ROK) here this evening.
</P>
<P>
The delegation, comprised of parliamentarians from three major
ROK political parties, is here at the invitation of the
International Department of the Central Committee of the Communist
Party of China (CPC).
</P>
<P>
Hu said that Sino-ROK relations in various fields have seen
many achievements since the two countries forged diplomatic ties,
and the leaders of the two countries have decided to establish a
cooperative partnership oriented towards the next century. China
is ready to work together with the ROK to build a mutually
beneficial, healthy and stable bilateral relationship, he added.
</P>
<P>
Hu, also a member of the Standing Committee of the Political
Bureau of the CPC Central Committee, said that increasing
exchanges between the CPC and major ROK parties will be
significant for the growth of Sino-ROK cooperative ties. He also
expressed the belief that bilateral relations will be reinforced
through joint efforts of statesmen and frank exchanges between the
political parties of the two countries.
</P>
<P>
Lee Sei Kee, head of the delegation, told Hu that the ROK's
major political parties share a common understanding in promoting
ROK-China relations, though they have differences in other areas.
</P>
<P>
The growth of ROK-China ties will benefit peace and stability
in Asia during a complex international situation, Lee said.
</P>
<P>
He went on to say that the delegation hopes to increase mutual
understanding and trust through its present China tour and
contribute to the development of bilateral ties.
</P>
<P>
The ROK visitors also expressed their appreciation for China's
constructive role in maintaining peace and stability on the Korean
Peninsula.
</P>
<P>
During the meeting, Hu briefed the delegation on the current
situation in China. 
</P>
</TEXT>
