<HEADLINE> China Reinsurance Company Aims For World's Top Ten </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NANJING, April 2 (Xinhua) -- Dai Fengju, general manager of the
China Reinsurance Company (China Re), said here today that the
company expects to elbow into the world's top ten within ten years.
</P>
<P>
Dai made the remark at an ongoing nationwide conference on
reinsurance. China Re plans to develop into a modern insurance
company based on international standards, he added.
</P>
<P>
China Re grew out of the Reinsurance Company under the
People's Insurance Corporation of China (PICC) which was disbanded
in October 1998, and its subsidiaries, including life insurance,
property insurance and reinsurance companies, have all become
state-owned independent insurers.
</P>
<P>
This March, China Re was established with registered capital of
three billion yuan, including 100 million U.S. dollars.
</P>
<P>
Dai said that China Re is scheduled to set up subsidiaries in
both Shanghai and Shenzhen within the year, and begins preparatory
work for the establishment of representative offices in Hong Kong
and Macao.  
</P>
</TEXT>
