<HEADLINE> Leading Scientists Appointed Visiting Professors </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 2 (Xinhua) -- A ceremony was held today at the
Great Hall of the People in Beijing to appoint 73 renowned Chinese
scientists as visiting scholars at 40 major Chinese universities,
and to grant awards to a number of outstanding scholars.
</P>
<P>
The ceremony was part of the Cheung Kong scholar promotion
program sponsored jointly by the Ministry of Education and Li Ka-
shing, chairman of the Hong Kong-based Cheung Kong Holding Company,
who has donated 70 million HK dollars to the program.
</P>
<P>
China's Vice-Premier Li Lanqing attended today's ceremony. Li,
who is also a member of the Standing Committee of the Political
Bureau of the Central Committee of the Communist Party of China,
congratulated the scholars and encouraged them to work harder to
help China achieve its strategic goal of rejuvenating the nation
through science and education.
</P>
<P>
The Cheung Kong scholar promotion program consists of efforts
to woo leading scientists to Chinese universities and to reward
scholars of outstanding achievement.
</P>
<P>
Visiting scholars in the Cheung Kong program receive an annual
salary of 100,000 yuan, and each first class and second class
award winner in the program receives one million yuan and 500,000
yuan, respectively.  
</P>
