<HEADLINE> Li Peng Leaves Greece for Turkey </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CRETE, Greece, April 2 (Xinhua) -- Li Peng, chairman of the
Standing Committee of the National People's Congress of China,
ended his official visit to Greece and left here on Friday for
Turkey, the second leg of his six-nation tour.
</P>
<P>
In his departing message to President of the Greek Parliament,
Apostolos Kaklamanis, Li Peng expressed his gratitude for the
warm welcome and hospitality accorded him by Kaklamanis and the
Greek parliament.
</P>
<P>
Li Peng said that during his visit to Greece, he exchanged
views with Kaklamanis and other leaders on promting relations
between the Chinese and Greek legislatures and their two
countries' peoples.
</P>
<P>
They also held talks on issues of common concern, including the
current crisis in Yugoslavia, and reached wide-ranging consensus.
Li Peng said that such talks helped increase mutual understanding
and friendship between the two countries.
</P>
<P>
He believes that a Sino-Greek relationship -- based on equality
and mutual benefit as well as friendship between the two peoples --
could be developed and strengthened even moreso.
</P>
<P>
Li Peng arrived in Greece on Tuesday afternoon for a four-day
official visit. His trip will also take him to Turkey, Syria,
Pakistan, Bangladesh and Thailand. 
</P>
</TEXT>
