<HEADLINE> Chinese President Meets Yemeni Vice President </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 2 (Xinhua) -- It is China's basic foreign policy
to develop friendly cooperative ties with other developing nations,
President Jiang Zemin said here today while meeting with Yemeni
Vice President Abdo Rabo Mansour Hadi.
</P>
<P>
This is because China itself is a developing country, Jiang
said, adding that his country is ready to promote 21st-century
oriented friendship and cooperation with Yemen in accord with the
five principles of peaceful coexistence.
</P>
<P>
Jiang noted that friendly contacts between the two peoples have
a long history, adding that since the establishment of diplomatic
ties between the two nations 40 years ago, bilateral friendship
and cooperation have always maintained good momentum.
</P>
<P>
China firmly stands by the reunification of Yemen and
appreciates Yemen's adherence to the "one China" policy, Jiang
said.
</P>
<P>
He stated that the two countries have also conducted fruitful
cooperation in the economic and trade sectors, and expressed his
belief that such cooperation will be furthered and deepened
through concerted efforts.
</P>
<P>
China is pleased that the situation is stable in Yemen, which
has solved border issues with its neighboring nations by peaceful
means, Jiang said.
</P>
<P>
Hadi said bilateral friendly cooperative ties have enjoyed
continuous promotion during the past four decades, and his
government and people thank China for its unselfish assistance to
Yemen.
</P>
<P>
China, as an important and influential nation within the U.N.
Security Council, is a significant force for maintaining world
peace and stability, he said.
</P>
<P>
Hadi said Yemen appreciates China's support for the Middle East
peace process and voiced the hope that China will play its due
role in this process.
</P>
<P>
He conveyed greetings from President Ali Abdullah Saleh to
Jiang, who asked that his best wishes be returned to Saleh.
</P>
<P>
Hadi, who arrived here Wednesday for an official visit as guest
of his Chinese counterpart Hu Jintao, conferred with Hu on
Thursday.
</P>
<P>
In addition to Beijing, Hadi will travel to Shanghai and
Shenzhen. 
</P>
