<HEADLINE> Famous Beijing Avenue To Be Greener </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 2 (Xinhua) -- Both sides of Chang'an Avenue,
China's longest and the symbol of Beijing, will be planted with
more grass and trees to welcome the upcoming 50th anniversary of
the founding of the People's Republic of China on October 1.
</P>
<P>
An official from the Beijing municipal government revealed
today that 15 hectares of green land, equal to the size of
Tian'anmen Square, will emerge on both sides of the avenue this
year.
</P>
<P>
At present, there are 43.83 hectares of greenery along the 13
kilometer-long avenue.
</P>
<P>
According to the official, Tian'anmen Square itself also will
become greener, with 2.56 hectares of grass and trees planted
around the Square.
</P>
<P>
In addition, the official said, the municipal government will
plant more evergreens in Beijing to keep the city green all the
year round. 
</P>
