<HEADLINE> 9 Thai Villagers Killed on Thai-Myanmar Border </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, April 2 (Xinhua) -- Thailand's third army commander
Major General Sommai Vichavorn confirmed on Friday that nine Thai
villagers have been killed near the border with Myanmar.
</P>
<P>
Earlier reports quoted Thai border officials as saying the
killings took place in an area notorious as a drugs transit route
used by ethnic minority groups.
</P>
<P>
The nine men were captured by an unidentified Myanmar group
before they were killed. Their bodies were found in the Fang
district of Chiang Mai province in northern Thailand, about three
kilometers from the border. It was unknown when the killing took
place.
</P>
<P>
Sommai said the killings were a serious infringement of Thai
sovereignty.
</P>
<P>
"I is a serious action. The military is checking how it
happened, who they are and why they were in Thailand," he told
reporters. 
