<HEADLINE> Shanghainese Donate 100 Million Yuan to Project Hope </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, April 2 (Xinhua) -- The Project Hope has received
more than 100 million yuan in donations from some five million
Shanghai residents over the past five year, according to official
sources.
</P>
<P>
The donations have funded the establishment of 520 schools
across China and helped some 38,000 dropouts return to the
classroom.
</P>
<P>
Among these unselfish donors, Fu Ying, a retired worker
suffering from intestine cancer, donated 10,000 yuan of her
personal savings to the project, saying that "education is very
important for the younger generation, and they need money more
than an old lady like me."
</P>
<P>
Most impressive is the fact that hundreds of donors refused to
disclose their names. One such, under the pseudonym "Happy Man,"
donated a total of 48,000 yuan over the past four years, which has
helped 70 dropouts to resume their schooling. 
</P>
