<HEADLINE> Incentive Package Ready for Nigeria's Flying Eagles </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LAGOS, April 2 (Xinhua) -- Coca Cola Nigeria Limited has
announced a 1.15 million Nairas (about 12,800 U.S. Dollars)
incentive package for the national youth team of Flying Eagles if
the team wins the 10th World Youth Soccer Championship (WYC) which
will kick off on Saturday.
</P>
<P>
Seni Adetu, regional marketing manager of the company,
disclosed this on Thursday here during the presentation of the
incentive package to the Nigerian U-20 national team.
</P>
<P>
The money which would reach the team in phases as the
tournament progresses is in addition to the sum of 560,000 Nairas
(about 6,200 Dollars) which the company presented to both players
and coaches of the team to boost their preparation for the
championship.
</P>
<P>
According to the package, Coca Cola is offering each of the
team members 50,000 Nairas (about 556 Dollars) if they qualify for
the second round, 100,000 Nairas (1,112 Dollars) should they scale
through the second round.
</P>
<P>
The soft drink producers will also pay each member of Flying
Eagles 250,000 Nairas (about 2,780 Dollars) if they win the semi
final match, 500,000 Nairas (about 5,560 Dollars) for the final
match to win the trophy of the championship.
</P>
<P>
Adetu said the financial package was part of the company's
contribution to encourage the players and demonstrate Coca Cola's
commitment to the development of football in the West African
country.
</P>
<P>
"This is also in furtherance of Coca Cola's commitment to
seeing the Flying Eagles win the U-20 WYC trophy," Adetu was
quoted as saying.  
</P>
</TEXT>
