<HEADLINE> Chinese Vice-Premier Meets with Thai Princess Sirindhorn </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 2 (Xinhua) -- Chinese Vice-Premier Li Lanqing
met with Princess Maha Chakri Sirindhorn of Thailand here this
evening.
</P>
<P>
Li welcomed the Thai Princess to visit China again, and thanked
her for a great deal of work she has done for the good of China-
Thailand friendship.
</P>
<P>
Speaking highly of bilateral relations, Li said China cherishes
the traditional friendship with Thailand like two relatives. The
two nations have been sincere to each other and trusted each other
since the establishment of diplomatic ties 20-odd years ago, he
added.
</P>
<P>
Friendship and cooperation between the two nations cover
political, economic, science and technology, cultural and many
other fields, he said.
</P>
<P>
He expressed his belief that with joint efforts, China and
Thailand will bring a closer bilateral relationship into the new
century.
</P>
<P>
Li also held a dinner to welcome Princess Sirindhorn.
</P>
<P>
The princess arrived here this afternoon on a friendly visit at
the invitation of the Chinese government.  
