<HEADLINE> Australia, Vietnam Strengthen Economic, Trade Ties </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CANBERRA, April 2 (Xinhua) -- Economic and trade ties between
Australia and Vietnam have been strengthened in the past few years
due to efforts made by both countries.
</P>
<P>
Statistics disclosed in the press show that in 1998, two-way
trade between the two countries exceeded 1 billion Australian
dollars (630 million U.S. dollars), representing a growth of 40
percent from the previous year.
</P>
<P>
Total Australian investment in Vietnam was about 1.3 billion
Australian dollars (820 million U.S. dollars), involving
activities of more than 100 Australian companies.
</P>
<P>
The My Thuan bridge, which will be ready for opening in the
middle of next year, is the largest infrastructure project funded
through the aid budget by Australia.
</P>
</TEXT>
