<HEADLINE>   Hackett Sets Men's 400m Freestyle World Record </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, April 2 (Xinhua) -- Australia's Grant Hackett
smashed the men's 400 meters freestyle world record with a time of
3 minutes 35.01 seconds and won the event gold medal at the World
Short-Course Swimming Championships on Friday.
</P>
<P>
The old mark of 3:39.82 was set by his compatriot and friend
Ian Thorpe in Perth last September. 
