<HEADLINE> New Passenger Trains in Yunnan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUNMING, April 2 (Xinhua) -- A new passenger railway service
will start on May 1 this year in southwest China's Yunnan province
to coincide with the '99 International Horticulture Exposition
which will open in the provincial capital of Kunming.
</P>
<P>
Local authorities announced here today that the 206-km railway,
which links the Guangtong Railway Station near Kunming to Dali, a
picturesque city in the western part of Yunnan, was completed last
June and has since been open to freight trains only.
</P>
<P>
The new train service will not only provide convenience for
domestic and overseas tourists, but also add impetus to the
economic development in the western region of Yunnan, where a
variety of ethnic minorities reside.
</P>
<P>
The '99 International Horticulture Exposition is the first of
its kind ever hosted by China and will last six months ending on
October 31. Millions of Chinese and foreign tourists are expected
to visit Kunming and the rest of Yunnan for this gardening
extravaganza. 
</P>
</TEXT>
