<HEADLINE> Forum to Mark 50th Anniversary of Women's Federation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 2 (Xinhua) -- A forum marking the 50th
anniversary of the establishment of the All-China Women's
Federation (ACWF) was held today in the Great Hall of the People
in Beijing.
</P>
<P>
Gu Xiulian, vice-president of the ACWF, reviewed the
achievements made by her federation in safeguarding women's rights
and interests in the past 50 years, and noted that the ACWF has
experienced great social changes along with the People's Republic
of China.
</P>
<P>
She pointed out that the Communist Party's leadership is a
correct political orientation of the women's federation, and
tradition confirms that only by adhering to the Party's leadership
and guidance in women's development can the federation really
represent and safeguard women's fundamental interests.
</P>
<P>
She said the ACWF has always centered its work on economic
development, and noted the only way to realize women's
emancipation under the socialist system is to boost the social
productive forces.
</P>
<P>
"Amid the market competition nowadays, women's education and
cultivation are essential to their rights and opportunities to
seek equal participation and development," she said, adding that
there is still a long way to go in maintaining women's legitimate
rights and interests in the primary stage of socialism.
</P>
<P>
Chen Muhua, honorary president of the ACWF, urged those engaged
in women's development to earnestly study Marxism, Leninism, Mao
Zedong Thought, and especially Deng Xiaoping Theory, and direct
the work accordingly.
</P>
<P>
The forum was presided over by Peng Peiyun, a vice-chairwoman
of the Standing Committee of the National People's Congress.
</P>
<P>
To conclude the event, she asked women's federations at all
levels to emphasize theoretical study, political awareness and
healthy ethics, and work hard to improve the work of women's
development.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
