<HEADLINE> Sri Lanka troops Kill 15 Tamil Rebels </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, April 2 (Xinhua) -- Sri Lankan government troops
Thursday killed 15 Tamil rebels in operations in the north of the
country, the Defense Ministry said Friday.
</P>
<P>
A ministry spokesman said government troops Thursday on small
operation confronted a group of Tamil rebels killing two rebels at
Mutur.
</P>
<P>
On Thursday, troops observed a small group of rebels moving at
Uranikulam and engaged with small arms. The troops confirmed two
rebels were killed, the spokesman said.
</P>
<P>
The spokesman said around 7:35 A.M. Thursday in Paranthan area,
Troops engaged a group of terrorists with machine guns and arms.
The rebels retaliated with mortars. At least four rebels were
killed during the confrontation.
</P>
<P>
The same day afternoon in general area Paranthan, Troops on a
clearing patrol confronted a group of rebels. The troops confirmed
two terrorists were killed or injured.
</P>
<P>
Government troops operating ahead of defenses confronted a
group of terrorists numbering about 10 Thursday morning in north
of Karapadamarippu. One of them was killed, the spokesman said.
</P>
<P>
In another incident around 3:15 Thursday in north of Mankulam,
Troops on a fighting patrol confronted a group of terrorists and
engaged with machine guns and small arms. At least four rebels
were killed and one other was injured during the confrontation, he
added.
</P>
<P>
Tamil rebels have been waging a war against the Sri Lankan
government since 1983 for a separate state of their own in the
north and east of the country. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
