<HEADLINE> Chinese Vice-President Meets with Cambodian Defense Co-Ministers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 2 (Xinhua) -- Chinese Vice-President Hu Jintao
met with Cambodian Co-Ministers of Defense Tea Banh and Prince
Sisowath Sereyrath here this afternoon.
</P>
<P>
Hu said that Sino-Cambodian relations have witnessed fresh
development as major progress has been made in national
reconciliation and political stability in Cambodia. "We are very
pleased with such progress", he added.
</P>
<P>
China respects the choice of the Cambodian government and
people and appreciates the unique role of King Norodom Sihanouk in
maintaining political stability and promoting national
reconciliation in Cambodia, Hu noted.
</P>
<P>
The vice-president expressed thanks for the "one China"
position adhered to by the Cambodian government, saying that China
will continue to consolidate and advance Sino-Cambodian
cooperative relations oriented to the next century.
</P>
<P>
The co-ministers spoke highly of Cambodia-China ties and said
that Cambodia "deeply appreciates the unselfish support and aid"
from China in maintaining peace, stability and development in
Cambodia.
</P>
<P>
They told Hu that Cambodia would continue to stick to the "one
China" policy, enhance the mutual trust and the cooperation
between Cambodia and China, and take a friendly bilateral ties
into the 21st century.
</P>
<P>
Chinese State Councilor and Defense Minister Chi Haotian was
among those attending the meeting.  
</P>
