<HEADLINE> Cholera Claims 5 in E. Kenya </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NAIROBI, April 2 (Xinhua) -- Five people have died and sixteen
others admitted into a district hospital following a fresh
outbreak of cholera early this week in Mwingi District in Kenya's
Eastern Province.
</P>
<P>
Justus Dereva, public health officer of the district, said more
cholera victims were being received at the hospital, noting that
the disease was spreading rapidly in Migwani and central divisions
of the district, the Kenya Times newspaper reported Friday.
</P>
<P>
The officer said he had banned the hawking of all foodstuff and
maize roasting in the district in a bid to curb the spread of the
epidemic.
</P>
<P>
Health officials had already launched cholera prevention
campaigns and cautioned locals to ensure they adhered to high
hygienic standards to avoid contracting the disease, Dereva noted
.
</P>
<P>
One person in Mbeere district of the same province reportedly
died of cholera last week.
</P>
<P>
Mbeere District Commissioner Rashid Mohammed said medical
personnel acted swiftly to control the spread of other areas and
that the disease had been contained in the district.
</P>
<P>
Last month, the outbreak of cholera claims at least 28 people
in the eastern Coast Province. 
</P>
</TEXT>
