<HEADLINE> UAE to Provide Aid to Kosovars </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ABU DHABI, April 2 (Xinhua) -- A charity group of the United
Arab Emirates (UAE) will send a delegation to Albania and
Macedonia on Saturday to provide financial and material aid to
Kosovan refugees, the Gulf News daily reported on Friday.
</P>
<P>
The delegation will buy food, clothing, blankets and other
items from the Macedonian markets to provide thousands of Kosovan
refugees who have fled alleged massacres committed by Serbian
forces, Ahmed Youssuf, executive manager of the Ajman-based Human
Appeal International (HAI), was quoted by the paper as saying.
</P>
<P>
"We are going to buy items for the 250,000 dirhams (about
68,300 U.S. dollars) we have already raised during the first
few days of the countrywide fund-raising campaign we launched to
help the people of Kosovo," he said.
</P>
<P>
Kosovo is a province of the Serbia Republic of Yugoslavia,
where most of the residents are ethnic Albanians.
</P>
<P>
Youssuf added that the delegation will also try to gather
information about the needs of the Albanian refugees in the
Balkans.
</P>
<P>
"Our delegation will prepare a detailed report about the
number of refugees and their needs," he said.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, Youssuf said that HAI had launched a UAE wide
campaign to collect money and other donations to be sent to
the Albanians who have poured out of Kosovo.
</P>
<P>
He said HAI will also organize other humanitarian campaigns
in the Gulf region "to raise as much money as possible to
bring relief to refugees in the Balkans."
</P>
<P>
The UAE last week expressed its support for NATO's on-going
air strikes against Yugoslavia, saying it was the only option
left to end the tragedy in Kosovo. 
</P>
