<DATE_TIME> 1999-04-02 08:35 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Strong Performance Seen in Cyprus' Stock </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NICOSIA, April 2 (Xinhua) -- The Cyprus Stock Market took
market players by surprise with a forceful upward trend during the
first quarter of 1999, a weekly market review said Friday.
</P>
<P>
The review, issued by the Cyprus Investment and Securities
Corporation Limited (CISCO), said even those who cited prospects
for 1999 based on the most optimistic scenarios, would not have
expected such a strong market performance.
</P>
<P>
Total volume of transactions hit 348.9 million pounds (697.8
million U.S. dollars), surpassing the total for the whole year of
1998 which stood at 348.1 million pounds (696.2 million dollars).
</P>
<P>
The average daily volume of transactions for the period rose to
5.8 million pounds (11.6 million dollars) as compared to that of
1998 which was 1.4 million pounds (2.8 million dollars).
</P>
<P>
The market rally was triggered by an announcement of the
Cyprus Popular Bank in January of its intention to acquire three
insurance companies belonging to the Schacolas Group of Companies.
</P>
<P>
Spectacular gains by the three insurance titles dragged
several other titles into a frenzy ascent.
</P>
<P>
Later on, an announcement by the Bank of Cyprus in January of
its "Centenary Gift" to shareholders brought afresh a wave of
euphoria among investors.
</P>
<P>
The CISCO All-Share Index closed at 509 points on January 29,
exhibiting a capital appreciation of 12.1 percent from year end.
</P>
<P>
January volume of transactions also shot up at unprecedented
levels, reaching 79.6 million Cyprus pounds (159.2 million
dollars), thus by far exceeded 1998's highest level recorded in
April, 45.6 million pounds (91.2 million dollars).
</P>
<P>
The "buying-mania" which hit the stock market assumed epidemic
proportions in February.
</P>
<P>
The CISCO All-Share Index reached the 600-point level covering
ground of 100 points within just 14 trading days, while it took
almost three years for the market to regain the all-time high
record of 522 points.
</P>
<P>
The CISCO All-Share Index closed at 585.6 points on February 26.
</P>
<P>
The market sustained an overall rising course in March.
</P>
<P>
The news of a stock split by Popular Bank further boosted
investor psychology, and as a result the market witnessed a new
all-time high of 626.1 points on March 23.
</P>
<P>
However, the ongoing NATO strikes in Yugoslavia seemed to
negatively impinge on market psychology.
</P>
<P>
The market was on a gradual descending trend since the strikes
were launched on March 24, with the CISCO All-Share Index closing
at 582.9 points on March 31. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19990402.0180 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-04-02 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Ningxia Makes Progress in Sino-German Afforestation Project </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YINCHUAN, April 2 (Xinhua) -- Northwest China's Ningxia Hui
Autonomous Region has planted 3,845 ha of forest since it began a
Sino-German afforestation project in 1996.
</P>
<P>
The project, initiated in 1994 by the Sino-German Committee on
Economy and Trade, involves 12 million deutsche marks (six million
U.S. dollars) from the German side and 62.19 million yuan (7.5
million U.S. dollars) from the Chinese side.
</P>
<P>
The afforestation project, which aims to create a tree belt
covering 8,550 ha. by the year 2000 and enclosing 30,000 ha of
forest in the Helan Mountains in the western part of the
autonomous region, is being carried out in seven counties and
cities.
</P>
<P>
Shizuishan, an industrial city in the northern part of the
region, has planted 228 ha. of forest since 1996, accounting for
45.5 percent of the set target.
</P>
<P>
The annual precipitation of the city, which borders on the
Tengger and Mu Us deserts in the west, was less than 200 mm.
</P>
</TEXT>
