<HEADLINE> China Puts First Boeing 737-800 Into Service </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NINGBO, April 2 (Xinhua) -- Hainan Airlines has recently
brought into service a Boeing 737-800 passenger plane, the first
in China.
</P>
<P>
Based in Haikou, the capital of south China's Hainan Province,
the airline will use the plane on two domestic air routes that
link this coastal city of Ningbo in east China's Zhejiang Province
with Beijing and Haikou.
</P>
<P>
The Boeing 737-800 has a higher cruise speed and greater range
than earlier models, and boasts significant improvements in noise
reduction, fuel consumption and maintenance costs.
</P>
<P>
Hainan Airlines is China's first joint-stock aviation company,
with a fleet of 26 aircraft, including 14 Boeing 737s.
</P>
<P>
A source with the airlines said it will buy another three
Boeing 737-800s and two Boeing 767s this year.  
</P>
