<HEADLINE> Russia Prosecutor General Suspended </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, April 2 (Xinhua) -- Russian President Boris Yeltsin on
Friday issued an order to suspend Prosecutor General Yuri Skuratov
while he is under investigation for alleged abuse of power in
connection with a sex scandal.
</P>
<P>
As Skuratov's conduct had been the subject of an inquiry by the
justice department, said Yeltsin, he had written to the Federation
Council, or the upper house of parliament, for the second time
this year, to request his dismissal.
</P>
<P>
On February 2, Yeltsin proposed to sack Skuratov after
receiving his resignation on "health reason." But the council, by
constitution the only body with the power to dismiss Skuratov,
rejected the proposal by a 142-6 vote.
</P>
<P>
Skuratov said before the voting that his on-going corruption
and bribery probes annoyed some ex-officials and financial
oligarchs, who were eager for his stepping down. 
</P>
