<HEADLINE> Heat Continues Losing Misery after Mashburn Return </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, April 1 (Xinhua) -- Miami Heat forward Jamal
Mashburn, returning after an absence of two months, scored 18
points on Thursday but could not stop the Heat's misery streak
with an 88-84 loss to the Philadelphia 76ers, the fifth setback in
six games.
</P>
<P>
As the first player off the bench, Mashburn made his first two
shots and finished 7-of-13 from the field, adding six rebounds and
three assists.
</P>
<P>
Mashburn got off to a quick start for the Heat this season,
recording 42 points, 13 rebounds and 11 assists in the first two
games of the season.
</P>
<P>
Detroit Pistons forward Christian Laettner will miss two weeks
due to a fractured rib suffered in the 107-75 victory over the
Chicago Bulls in Michigan.
</P>
<P>
Laettner, who missed the season's first 22 games due to a
ruptured Achilles tendon, absorbed an elbow to the ribs from
Chicago forward Mark Bryant with 48 seconds left in the third
quarter and did not return.
</P>
<P>
The 29-year-old Laettner averaged 8.5 points and 4.3 rebounds
in 10 games since being reunited with former college teammate
Grant Hill. The Pistons (20-12) acquired Laettner from the Atlanta
Hawks during the offseason.
</P>
<P>
Detroit has won six straight games and pulled within one-half
game of Indiana for first place in the Central Division with
Thursday's victory.
</P>
<P>
Rookie Vince Carter scored 31 points, including six in the
final 1:10, as the Toronto Raptors won their seventh straight home
game, edging Indiana Pacers 88-87.
</P>
<P>
Carter had 11 rebounds, six assists, two blocks and two steals
for the Raptors, who beat the Pacers for the first time ever after
13 losses.
</P>
<P>
Toronto improved its overall record to 16-14, matching its
victory total for all last season.
</P>
