lost its third in a row and dropped behind Philadelphia and
Toronto in the race for the Eastern Conference's eighth and final
playoff spot.
</P>
<P>
In New Jersey, Stephon Marbury and Keith Van Horn helped the
Nets overcome a 14-point second-half deficit to beat Hawks 90-85,
but All-Star center Jayson Williams broke his right leg with 50.9
seconds left in the final minute and will miss the rest of the
season.
</P>
<P>
In Dallas, Michael Finley scored 22 points, including three key
baskets down the stretch, as the Mavericks ended a five-game
losing streak after upset LA Clippers 93-84. Gary Trent had 23
points and 10 rebounds and Shawn Bradley added 16 points and 13
rebounds for the Mavericks, who had lost eight of their previous
nine.
</P>
<P>
In San Antonio, Tim Duncan scored a career-high 39 points to
lead the San Antonio Spurs over the Vancouver Grizzlies 103-91 for
its 15th victory in 17 games despite playing without center David
Robinson, who missed the game with an inflamed left knee.
</P>
<P>
Duncan was 19-of-31 from the field and grabbed 13 rebounds. He
topped his previous scoring high of 35, against Golden State last
season.
</P>
<P>
In Denver, Chauncey Billups had a career-high 32 points and Van
Exel added 31 as the Denver Nuggets beat the Seattle SuperSonics
113-110.
</P>
<P>
Billups was 10-for-18 from the field, including 4-of-9 on 3-
pointers. Van Exel was 11-for-23, including 6-of-10 from long
range.
</P>
<P>
Gary Payton had 33 points and 11 assists for the SuperSonics,
who dropped to 4-11 on the road this year.
</P>
<P>
In Salt Lake City, Karl Malone sank a jumper with 2.7 seconds
left to cap a big rally by Utah, which overcame a 15-point deficit
in the fourth quarter to squeeze Rockets 88-87.
</P>
<P>
The win stopped Houston's nine-game winning streak and kept the
Jazz in first place in the Midwest Division.
</P>
<P>
Hakeem Olajuwon, who had 32 points, including the 25,000th of
his career.
</P>
<P>
The Jazz won at home for the 25th time in their last 26 games
and beat Houston for the seventh straight time. 
</P>
