<HEADLINE> New Book Focuses on Tibetan Culture, Religion and Philosophy </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LHASA, April 2 (Xinhua) -- A book has been published in
southwest China's Tibet Autonomous Region about Tibetan culture,
Buddhism and western philosophy.
</P>
<P>
Titled "New Thoughts -- Pondering on the Search for Tibetan
Buddhism", the book is regarded as a work of definitive research
in its comparisons of Tibetan and western culture and philosophy.
</P>
<P>
It also features research on the future of Tibetan philosophy
as well as evaluating Tibetan Buddhism.
</P>
<P>
Zongbue Cering Doje, the book's author, is one of the leading
researchers in many specific and profound aspects of Tibetan
Buddhism and philosophy.
