<HEADLINE> Chinese Bank Providing 40 Billion Yuan in Housing Loans </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 2 (Xinhua) -- The China Industrial and
Commercial Bank (CICB) announced today that it will provide 40
billion yuan in housing loans this year.
</P>
<P>
The bank's Vice-president Xie Duyang says that 25 billion yuan
of that will be used for individual buyers and the rest for
housing development.
</P>
<P>
He said that the bank has put the housing loans under special
management to ensure that it will not be misused.
</P>
<P>
In 1998, nearly 9 percent of the bank's new loans went for
housing credit, with 10.2 billion yuan for individual credit.
</P>
<P>
Xie says that individual credit has become a major business of
CICB and a concerted effort has been made in the past few years to
establish better control, organization, technology, and business
in the credit.
</P>
<P>
By the end of last year, CICB's collection rate of interest on
individual housing loans was 98 percent.
</P>
<P>
Xie has also told all bank branches to find more effective ways
to prevent risks in new loans while expanding the credit business.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
