<HEADLINE> Chinese Processing Enterprise Expand Foreign Operations (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The government encourages powerful machinery and electronics
enterprises to expand processing operations, especially operations
using domestic raw materials and equipment, in Africa, Central
Asia, the Middle East, Eastern Europe and South America.
</P>
<P>
A package of preferential policies will be introduced to assist
related enterprises, including simplified approval procedures,
export rebates and various other financial and insurance services.
</P>
<P>
The government will grant related enterprises priority in terms
of import-export rights and access to capital.
</P>
<P>
Addressing a recent national foreign trade conference, MOFTEC
Minister Shi Guangsheng said the ministry will encourage large and
medium-sized machinery and electronics manufacturing enterprises
to establish overseas plants, especially in Latin America and
Africa.
</P>
<P>
Related enterprises with appropriate capacities will be
encouraged to earmark investments for the establishment of
overseas operations to assemble manufactured parts, according to
Liu.  
