<HEADLINE> Chinese Processing Enterprises Expand Foreign Operations (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 2 (Xinhua) -- Major machinery and electronics
enterprises in China are in the process of increasing foreign
operations, according to an official with the Ministry of Foreign
Trade and Economic Cooperation (MOFTEC).
</P>
<P>
The Chunlan Group and TCL Group, two of the nation's major
household appliance manufacturers, plan to open manufacturing
plants in Russia, while major switchboard producers Julong
Corporation and Zhongxing Telecommunications Company have
announced plans to invest in Latin America and Africa.
</P>
<P>
Liu Yingjun, director of MOFTEC's Overseas Investment
Administration, said the ministry has consistently encouraged
processing enterprises with overseas operations to use domestic
equipment and materials.
</P>
<P>
MOFTEC will sponsor a training seminar in May as part of an
effort to help Chinese enterprises avoid unnecessary mistakes when
investing overseas.
</P>
<P>
The seminar, which will target chief executive officers and
potential overseas managers and executives, will feature language
training and information covering investment regulations and
target nations.
</P>
<P>
Observers noted that the government encouragement of
processing enterprise to invest overseas is part of an effort to
increase exports and establish a new growth point, as such
investment projects will promote the export of raw materials,
equipment and parts.
</P>
</TEXT>
