<HEADLINE> African States to Meet on Anti-Drugs </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The theme of the conference, to be held in Cape Town from April
8 to 10, will be "Total Commitment to the Eradication of Drugs,"
Daily Mail said Friday.
</P>
<P>
Drugs such as mantrap, cannabis resin (hashish), bhang, cocaine
and morphine have posed threats to the region, said the Director
of Criminal Investigations (DCI), Adadi Rajabu, and the National
Inter-ministerial Anti- Drug Commission, George Timbuka.
</P>
<P>
The officials also told the paper here Thursday that a special
campaign to expose all facets of drug transactions in the region
will be launched and intensified.
</P>
<P>
The crusade is meant to save the region from an impending
catastrophic threat posed by drug addicts among youths, Rajabu
said.
</P>
<P>
The DCI director called on all people to reject drug sales in
the neighborhood, noting that "it is not enough to say that drug
addiction is my neighbor's problem." He added that unified
regional efforts are of great importance.
</P>
<P>
SADC countries are collectively implementing some resolutions
passed during a drug conference in Abuja, Nigeria last year.
</P>
<P>
Abuse of illicit drugs on the continent is reported to be
growing while big African cities and seaports are increasingly
being used to transport heroin from Asia as well as cocaine from
South Africa to Europe, the International Narcotics Control Board
said. 
</P>
