<HEADLINE> Death Sentence for Zou Jingmeng Killers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 2 (Xinhua) -- The death sentence has been handed
down on two men who murdered Zou Jingmeng, former director of the
State Meteorological Bureau, in a robbery attempt in February. A
third accomplice was given life imprisonment,
</P>
<P>
The Beijing's No.1 Intermediate People's Court today passed
sentence on Ma Ke, 18, and Jiang Tao, 46, for the killing of Zou,
late member of the Standing Committee of the National Committee of
the Chinese People's Political Consultative Conference.
</P>
<P>
All property owned by the two men will be confiscated by the
state and they will be deprived of their political rights.
</P>
<P>
Their accomplice Han Shulong, 21, was also deprived of his
political rights all his life and fined 5,000 yuan.
</P>
<P>
Zou, who served as the president of the World Meteorological
Organization between 1987 and June 1995, died from injuries
sustained during the robbery attempt in Beijing's Haidian district
on February 22.
</P>
<P>
Born in 1929, Zou joined the Communist Party of China in 1948.
He served as director of the former State Meteorological Bureau (
China Meteorological Administration) between 1982-1996 and had
been honorary director of the administration since October 1996.
</P>
<P>
The late senior official was an alternate member of the 12th,
13th and 14th central committees of the Communist Party of China
convened between 1982-1992.  
</P>
</TEXT>
