<DATE_TIME> 1999-04-02 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Values Talented Senior Citizens </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHENYANG, April 2 (Xinhua) -- China is experimenting with a
market mechanism which enables talented senior citizens to
negotiate for better positions.
</P>
<P>
The mechanism is based on "competitive salary negotiations",
which asks talented senior citizens to present speeches to justify
salary requests before representatives from participating
enterprise bid for their services.
</P>
<P>
The Shenyang Job Placement Market in northeast China's Liaoning
Province sponsored the first senior citizens talent fair in 1998.
Various companies attending the event hired 12 talented senior
citizens for annual salaries ranging between 20,000-100,000 yuan.
</P>
<P>
Annual salaries of 100,000 yuan are commonplace in various
other countries, but are several times the average for talented
Chinese senior citizens.
</P>
<P>
Similar talent fairs have since been held in Shanghai city and
the provinces of Guangdong, Sichuan and Jilin.
</P>
<P>
Only scores of senior citizens participated in the 1998 Shenyang
fair. However, the second fair held earlier this year attracted
over 1,000 participants, with negotiated salaries ranging between
100,000-400,000 yuan.
</P>
<P>
Economist Lin Muxi, a professor at Liaoning University, noted
that China's effort to develop a knowledge-based economy has
created a highly competitive environment forcing enterprises to
bid for talented people. The experiment involving talented senior
citizens will have far-reaching significance, according to Lin.
</P>
<P>
According to an official, the Ministry of Personnel is
developing a scientific system to assess and determine the
appropriate salary range for talented senior citizens.
</P>
<P>
Liaoning Province, one of China's heavy industrial bases, is
home to 10 percent of the country's large and medium-sized
enterprises.
</P>
<P>
China's first job placement market, which was founded in
Shenyang in the early 1980s, sparked the establishment of over 2,
000 related markets nationwide. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19990402.0210 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-04-02 </DATE_TIME>
