<HEADLINE> BOC Sets Up Risk Control Department </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 2 (Xinhua) -- The Bank of China (BOC) announced
today that it has established a risk-control department in it's
headquarters in Beijing.
</P>
<P>
A bank spokesman said that the establishment of the new
department aims to reinforce risk management of credit businesses
with various non-financial institutional clients.
</P>
<P>
He said that the risk-control department will also participate
in formulating credit policies, draft basic rules for credit risk
management, supervise the implementation of credit business
policies, and organize and manage the BOC's unified credit
granting.
</P>
<P>
This is the first time a state-owned commercial bank has
established a risk-control system, the spokesman said.
</P>
<P>
As China's largest foreign exchange bank, the BOC realized
profits of 3.203 billion yuan in 1998, and so far the number of
its overseas institutions has reached 554.  
</P>
