<HEADLINE> China Enhances Reliability of Large Power Generators </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 2 (Xinhua) -- The reliability of large Chinese-
made power-generating units operating in the country with
capacities of more than 100 megawatts has risen to over 90 percent,
up three percentage points from 1997.
</P>
<P>
The enhanced reliability represents a marked improvement in
both the safe operation and economic efficiency of the country's
large generators, according to a senior official with the China
State Power Corporation today.
</P>
<P>
He said that China has introduced a reliability monitoring and
management system aimed at solving common quality problems, which
has proved to be very effective.
</P>
<P>
Under the system, construction workers and power equipment
manufacturers work together on the installation and trial
operations of new generators. Both sides cooperate to solve any
defects during the test run, especially those that might lead to
accidents.
</P>
<P>
The official cited the latest statistics showing that by the
end of last year, the country's total installed capacity had
reached 300,000 megawatts, of which more than 60 percent was
contributed by large generating units with capacities above 100
megawatts.
</P>
<P>
Experts here noted that the favorable change in the structure
of generating units signals rapid improvement in China's power
sector.  
</P>
</TEXT>
