<HEADLINE> Beijing to Host Piano, Violin Contests </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 2 (Xinhua)-- The Second Mido Piano Contest and
First Mido Violin Contest will be held in Beijing between July 8-
13, according to the Central Conservatory of Music and the France-
China Cultural Exchange Committee.
</P>
<P>
Contestants will perform works created by Chinese and French
composers. All contestants will be required to compete in the
primary selection process prior to reaching the final competition.
The panel of judges will consist of well-known musicians from both
countries. The list of awards will include scholarships to study
music in France.
</P>
<P>
The France-China Cultural Exchange Committee was founded by
French-Chinese pianist Chow Ching Ling. Chow taught at the Central
Conservatory of Music and has devoted herself to promoting
cultural exchange between the two nations since returning to
France some 20 years ago. 
</P>
</TEXT>
