<HEADLINE> Major Romanian Paper Condemns NATO Bombing on Yugoslavia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUCHAREST, April 1 (Xinhua) -- Romania's leading daily Adevarul
(Truth) Thursday lashed out at the U.S.-led NATO for its
aggression on Yugoslavia, a sovereign country, under the excuse of
defending human rights and peace.
</P>
<P>
NATO's bombing on Yugoslavia does not at all aim to achieve "
peace", as the military bloc has claimed, but is solely designed
to stage a war, said a commentary in the newspaper written by its
editor-in-chief Cristian Tudor Popescu.
</P>
<P>
If NATO did pursue peace sincerely, it would not have rejected
diplomatic efforts from any side, said the commentary entitled "
NATO Bullets."
</P>
<P>
NATO's insincerity was already revealed prior to Russian Prime
Minister Yevgeny Primakov's trip to Yugoslavia for mediation, the
commentary said. Senior NATO officials had said Primakov's tour
would be in vain unless Yugoslav President Slobodan Milosevic
agreed to "immediately and unconditionally withdraw all troops
from Kosovo."
</P>
<P>
Now the air strikes launched by NATO have claimed thousands of
lives in Yugoslavia, resulting in the kind of "human disaster"
that NATO said "it has been trying to prevent," said the
commentary.
</P>
<P>
It said the reason that the United States deemed the peace
proposal made by Milosevic after talks with Primakov as "far from
enough" and "unacceptable" was that Washington could not stand
Russia's efforts to restore peace to the Balkans.
</P>
<P>
The life and death of people in the hinterland of Europe does
not count much to the United States. What the United States wants
is precisely to bring Yugoslavia down to its knees in a pool of
blood and submit the whole Europe so that the United States can
pose itself as one that dominates the world.
</P>
<P>
The commentary said that the United States is trying to
strangle a sovereign country by the most typical means employed by
Adolf Hitler.
</P>
<P>
U.S. President Bill Clinton's remark that "Yugoslavia is
jeopardizing international support for Serb claims to Kosovo"
clearly shows that he is instigating Kosovo's secession from
Yugoslavia. 
</P>
