<HEADLINE> Thompson Sets Women's 100m Medley World Record </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, April 2 (Xinhua) -- Jennifer Thompson of United
States set a world record at the women's 100 meters individual
medley with a time of 59.30 seconds here Friday morning at the
fourth heat of the World Short Course Swimming Championships.
</P>
<P>
Thompson became the first women to break one minute in the
distance. She surpassed the previous mark of 1:00.35 created just
minutes before by Slovakia's Matina Moravcova in the previous heat.
</P>
<P>
Moravcova shaved 0.06 of a second off the previous record 1:00.
41 set by Thompson in January 1999 in Sydney. 
