<HEADLINE> Romania Provides Humanitarian Aid to Kosovo Refugees </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUCHAREST, April 1 (Xinhua) -- The Romanian government decided
Thursday to provide humanitarian aid for Macedonia to help the
Kosovan refugees fleeing there.
</P>
<P>
The decision came a week after Macedonia asked Romania for help.
</P>
<P>
Government spokesman Adriana Saftoiu said the aid, valued at
nine billion lei (600,000 U.S. dollars), includes milk powder,
cooking oil, sugar, medicine, clothing and quilts.
</P>
<P>
