which will total 250,000 lei (16,667 dollars), to Kosovans who are
taking refuge in the northwest of the country.
</P>
<P>
On March 26, Romania announced it would take up to 4,000
refugees from Macedonia in response to a request for help.
</P>
<P>
After NATO began its air strikes against Yugoslavia last
Wednesday, thousands of Yugoslav refugees have fled to neighboring
countries.
</P>
<P>
By Friday, altogether 101 Kosovo refugees had arrived in
Romania, according to Romanian official statistics, but officials
in charge of immigration noted that the actual number is far more.
