<HEADLINE> MD-90 Program Proceeds Smoothly </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHENYANG, April 2 (Xinhua) -- Industrial sources report that
China's MD-90 passenger aircraft program is proceeding smoothly.
</P>
<P>
The Shenyang Aircraft Industrial Corporation shipped a tail
assembly and wireless communications and power equipment to the
Shanghai Aircraft Plant during March. Related equipment will be
used to complete the second MD-90 to be assembled in China.
</P>
<P>
The program for manufacturing major component and assembling MD-
90s was introduced in 1990. China signed a 1995 agreement with
McDonnell Douglas calling for aircraft plants in Shanghai, Chengdu,
Shenyang and Xi'an to assemble 20 MD-90s.
</P>
<P>
The first MD-90 assembled in China entered operations last year.
