<HEADLINE>   Duncan Named NBA Player of the Month </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, April 1 (Xinhua) -- San Antonio forward Tim Duncan,
who helped lead the Spurs to an NBA-best 14-2 record last month,
today was named NBA Player of the Month for games played in March.
</P>
<P>
Duncan started all 16 games for the Spurs and averaged 23.5
points, 10.9 rebounds, 2.94 blocked shots, and 1.31 steals in 39
minutes per game.
</P>
<P>
He shot 149-for-286 from the field and ranked third in scoring
fourth in shot blocking, and eighth in rebounding and field-goal
percentage among league leaders for the month.
</P>
<P>
Duncan had nine double-doubles in March and led San Antonio in
scoring 14 times and in rebounding 10 times. He scored 20 or more
points 12 times and grabbed 10 or more rebounds 10 times.
</P>
<P>
He had several standout performances during the month including
a season-high 34 points, 13 rebounds, four assists, three steals
and three blocked shots in a 106-96 win at Denver on March 7, and
17 points and a season-high tying 17 rebounds in the Spurs' 82-78
win at Golden State on March 17.
</P>
<P>
Other candidates for NBA Player of the Month were Houston's
Charles Barkley, Milwaukee's Glenn Robinson, Minnesota's Kevin
Garnett, Orlando's Darrell Armstrong, Philadelphia's Allen Iverson
and Phoenix's Jason Kidd. 
</P>
</TEXT>
