<TEXT>
<P>
TIRANA, April 1 (Xinhua) -- Albanian Prime Minister Pandeli
Majko said Thursday the only solution to the Kosovo crisis was to
deploy NATO troops in the Yugoslav province.
</P>
<P>
During a meeting with Charles Josselin, secretary of state to
the French foreign ministry in charge of cooperation, Majko said
the situation in Kosovo was very serious and it was imperative to
find a way out.
</P>
