to force Milosevic to accept a peace plan mainly proposed by the
United States and its allies at the Paris peace talks.
</P>
<P>
Albania has urged NATO to deploy ground forces in Kosovo, but U.
S. President Bill Clinton has ruled this out.
</P>
<P>
Since the air strikes started on March 24, Albania has been
burdened by a great influx of refugees as more than 22,000 Kosovo
refugees have limped into the poorest country in Europe. 
