<P>
In addition, the Romanian government also decided to provide
food, clothing and medicines valued at 250 million lei (166,666
dollars) to Yugoslav refugees fleeing to southern Romanian towns
of Caras-Severin and Timis.
</P>
<P>
Earlier, Romania received 3,000 to 4,000 Kosovo refugees from
Macedonia under request. 
</P>
