The sole male athlete was Wang Yifu, who won four gold medals
at the World Shooting Championships in 1998 and two berths to the
2000 Sydney Olympic Games. Wang was awarded the Best Ten honour
for the third time after 1992 and 1994.
</P>
<P>
Lee Lai Shan, the first champion for Hong Kong in Asian Games
last year and runner-up in the World Windsurfing Championships,
was the second Hong Kong athlete to win the award after cyclist
Wong Kam Po last year.
</P>
<P>
Swimmer Chen Hua, speedskater Yang Yang and Lee Lai Shan, who
were taking part in the international competition at the same time,
were absent from the awarding ceremony. 
