<HEADLINE> Portland's Mike Dunleavy Named NBA Coach of the Month </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, April 1 (Xinhua) -- Mike Dunleavy, who guided the
Portland Trail Blazers to a 15-3 record in March, today was named
NBA Coach of the Month.
</P>
<P>
The Trail Blazers were 9-1 at home and 6-2 on the road in March.
They limited opponents to a league-low 39.6 floor shooting and 86.
6 points per game during the month.
</P>
<P>
Under Dunleavy, Portland has roared to a league-best 24-6 mark
and a four-game lead over the highly touted Los Angeles Lakers in
the Pacific Division.
</P>
<P>
Dunleavy also has a deep and talented squad, but he has done a
nice job of finding minutes for as many players as possible.
</P>
<P>
The Blazers have five players averaging between 12 and 16
points per game and 10 averaging at least 10 minutes per contest.
</P>
<P>
"What he's doing with his team -- getting them to accept lesser
and loving it -- is a tremendous accomplishment. It really is, "
Philadelphia 76ers coach Larry Brown said.
</P>
<P>
Other candidates included Rudy Tomjanovich of Houston, George
Karl of Milwaukee, Chuck Daly of Orlando, Gregg Popovich of San
Antonio and Butch Carter of Toronto.
</P>
<P>
Utah Jazz coach Jerry Sloan was honored in February. 
