<HEADLINE> Long-Distance Education System In Northern China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHIJIAZHUANG, April 2 (Xinhua) -- A long-distance education
system has begun at Teachers' University in China's Hebei Province.
</P>
<P>
The university was set up in 1996 by combining four colleges
and universities several dozen kilometers away from each other.
</P>
<P>
The distance between them causes inconveniences for staff
members and high fuel costs for transportation. Average annual
fuel costs and maintenance of buses for the regular runs between
branch campuses are as much as a million yuan.
</P>
<P>
The university started work on a long-distance multimedia
education system to link the branch campuses and to provide a
varied education, data, reference, and information services, and
lectures, research services, exchanges, and discussions via the
computer network.
</P>
<P>
The university has completed the first phase and the whole
project is expected to be completed in early 2000. 
