<HEADLINE> Qian Qichen Stresses Governing of Macao According to Law (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
He said that the "one country, two systems" principle is the
essential part of the Basic Law and provides a concrete expression
of it and a legal framework for it.
</P>
<P>
The Basic Law gives the MSAR a high degree of autonomy in
administration, legislation, and the judiciary and the power of
final adjudication.
</P>
<P>
Also, it says that everything in the SAR is to be administered
by the permanent residents of Macao themselves and this
demonstrates the high-degree of trust and support of the SAR by
the central government.
</P>
<P>
Qian reviewed the SAR Preparatory Committee's work since it was
establishment last May and said a Selection Committee for the
First SAR Government is expected to be formed this month. It will
be responsible for electing the candidate for the position of SAR
chief executive who will be appointed by the central people's
government and who will then form the first SAR government in
accordance with the NPC decision and the Basic Law.
</P>
<P>
Qian said that negotiations with Portugal on a smooth
transition and the handover ceremony are under way and he believes
that all transition matters can be solved through cooperation.
</P>
<P>
The forum was held in the Great Hall of the People and presided
over by Jiang Chunyun, vice-chairman of the Standing Committee of
the National People's Congress.
</P>
<P>
Susana Chou, Xiao Weiyun, Lau Cheok Va, and Wu Jianpan, members
of the Committee to Draft the Basic Law of the Macao SAR, also
spoke at the meeting. 
</P>
