<HEADLINE> Myanmar Produces 360,000 Tons of Cement in 1998 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YANGON, April 2 (Xinhua) -- Myanmar produced a total of 364,959
tons of cement in 1998, 150,723 tons less than that in 1997 when
it was 515,682 tons, according to the latest economic indicators
published by the country's Central Statistical Organization.
</P>
<P>
Cement has become more and more in demand in Myanmar day by day
as the country geared up its pace in recent years in building
infrastructure facilities including motor roads and bridges.
</P>
<P>
In 1998, Myanmar imported 68 million U.S. dollars' worth of
cement, while in 1997, the cement it bought was valued at 75
million dollars.
</P>
<P>
In order to meet domestic demand, Myanmar has planned to build
a large-scale cement factory at a cost of 150 million dollars to
produce 4,000 tons of cement annually. 
</P>
