<HEADLINE> Brazil's Stocks Rise 20 Percent in March </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
RIO DE JANEIRO, APRIL 1 (Xinhua)-- The Bovespa Index, that
shows the evolution of shares' most negotiated prices on the Sao
Paulo Stock Market, the largest one in Latin America, rose 20.04
percent in March, stockmarket sources said on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
With this positive result, the Bovespa Index has increased in
value by 57.67 percent in the first three months of the year.
</P>
<P>
Furthermore, the American dollar fell last month, its
commercial value diminished by 15.69 percent, after the real
reached 2.04 per dollar at the beginning of last March closing at
1.72 reales.
</P>
<P>
Analysts of the market specified that the return of foreign
funds to this South American country had an effect on the rise of
the market due to the fall of the greenback. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
